reviews.review: Not es bad as TLJ but still a mess.

Had really low expectations for this movie, but have to say that I enjoyed this one a lot more than I initially thought I was going to. Yea, I agree that the trilogy don't have a strong enough thread between the movies, but this movie was truly enjoyable and exiting - a lot better than the last Jedi in my opinion.

JJ Abrams has picked up the charred mess Rian Johnson left behind and has breathed new life into Star Wars. JJ has brought the true spirit of the franchise back to the screen in a massive mind-blowing story that ANSWERS QUESTIONS we have been waiting for since 2015 in a near 2 1/2 hour whirlwind of action, plot, and heart. It is frightening, beautiful and uplifting. I only wish I could have paused it every half hour to take in and digest what I had just seen before moving on. I have tickets to see it again this weekend.

Somehow jj managed to pick up the pieces of a franchise obliterated by rian Johnson and put a film together that regained the respect and happiness of fans, was exciting for audiences of all ages and finished the story off in a way that everyone could enjoy, except for all the unnecessary kissing

Who are these critics given it a rotten? It takes the ideas from previous films and wraps everything up. It has a couple neat twists, it looks great, takes a few chances here and there, and left me feeling good about Star Wars.  Is this movie perfect? No. But it's a damn sight better than plenty of movies.
Against other Star Wars movies, it stacks up among the best. It wasn't overly corny, or blatantly obvious, although it did play it safe. Great movie. Hopefully they make more!

We thought that it  brought everything together.
it made for a fitting end to the saga. Very action packed and answered many questions. Worth going to see.

I saw it, and it was amazing. A stupendous ending to this Saga, and such a moment for Rey and by extension, Daisy Ridley. I liked the Force Awakens. I liked the Last Jedi. This movie changed my life. I don't know if I'll ever have another movie experience like this. It was the culmination of so much, and it meant so much to me. Everyone please go see this movie!
